 {"id":"rust_proxy-7or","title":"Add atomic config reload mechanism with synchronization","description":"## Scope

Implement the atomic config reload mechanism that safely swaps the active configuration while the daemon is running, with proper synchronization to avoid race conditions.

## Rationale

Config reload must be atomic to prevent partial updates that could leave the daemon in an inconsistent state. For example, if we update the proxy list but crash before updating health check settings, we could have health checks running against stale proxy IDs.

## Implementation Details

### Config Holder with Arc<RwLock>

The daemon needs a shared, mutable config holder:

```rust
pub struct ConfigHolder {
    inner: Arc<RwLock<AppConfig>>,
    path: PathBuf,
}

impl ConfigHolder {
    pub fn new(config: AppConfig, path: PathBuf) -> Self {
        Self {
            inner: Arc::new(RwLock::new(config)),
            path,
        }
    }

    /// Get current config (cheap clone of Arc)
    pub async fn get(&self) -> AppConfig {
        self.inner.read().await.clone()
    }

    /// Attempt to reload config from disk
    /// Returns Ok(Some(diff)) if reload succeeded with changes
    /// Returns Ok(None) if config unchanged
    /// Returns Err if config invalid (keeps running with old config)
    pub async fn reload(&self) -> Result<Option<ConfigDiff>> {
        // 1. Load new config from disk
        let new_config = match AppConfig::load_from(&self.path) {
            Ok(c) => c,
            Err(e) => {
                tracing::error!(error = %e, "Failed to parse config, keeping current");
                return Err(e);
            }
        };

        // 2. Validate new config
        if let Err(e) = new_config.validate() {
            tracing::error!(error = %e, "New config invalid, keeping current");
            return Err(e.into());
        }

        // 3. Compute diff
        let old_config = self.inner.read().await;
        let diff = diff_configs(&old_config, &new_config);

        if diff.is_empty() {
            return Ok(None);
        }

        // 4. Log what's changing
        diff.log();

        // 5. Atomic swap
        drop(old_config);
        *self.inner.write().await = new_config;

        tracing::info!("Configuration reloaded successfully");
        Ok(Some(diff))
    }
}
```

### Thread Safety Considerations

- Use `RwLock` not `Mutex` - allows concurrent reads during normal operation
- Write lock only held briefly during swap
- All components that need config should hold `Arc<ConfigHolder>` and call `get()` when needed
- Avoid caching config in local variables for extended periods

### Handling Components That Need Notification

Some components need to react to config changes:
- Health check loop: may need to adjust interval
- Load balancer: may need to update proxy list

Use a broadcast channel for change notifications:

```rust
pub struct ConfigHolder {
    inner: Arc<RwLock<AppConfig>>,
    path: PathBuf,
    change_tx: broadcast::Sender<ConfigDiff>,
}

impl ConfigHolder {
    pub fn subscribe(&self) -> broadcast::Receiver<ConfigDiff> {
        self.change_tx.subscribe()
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- ConfigHolder provides thread-safe config access
- reload() atomically swaps config
- Invalid configs are rejected without affecting running config
- Change notifications sent to subscribers
- No race conditions during concurrent access and reload","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T18:55:48.314807599Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-21T17:28:27.374697940Z","compaction_level":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rust_proxy-7or","depends_on_id":"rust_proxy-7s9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-18T18:57:06.891793420Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","metadata":"","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"rust_proxy-7s9","title":"Implement config diff logic to detect what changed","description":"## Scope

Implement logic to compare two AppConfig instances and produce a structured diff describing what changed. This enables targeted reload (only update what changed) and clear logging.

## Rationale

Blind full reload is wasteful and potentially disruptive. By knowing exactly what changed, we can:
- Only restart components that need it
- Provide clear logging ("Added proxy 'new-proxy', changed health_check_interval from 30s to 60s")
- Avoid unnecessary connection disruption

## Implementation Details

### ConfigDiff Structure

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Default)]
pub struct ConfigDiff {
    /// Proxies that were added
    pub proxies_added: Vec<String>,
    /// Proxies that were removed
    pub proxies_removed: Vec<String>,
    /// Proxies whose config changed (id, field, old, new)
    pub proxies_modified: Vec<(String, String, String, String)>,
    /// Settings that changed (name, old, new)
    pub settings_changed: Vec<(String, String, String)>,
    /// Whether listen address changed (requires restart)
    pub listen_changed: bool,
}

impl ConfigDiff {
    pub fn is_empty(&self) -> bool {
        self.proxies_added.is_empty()
            && self.proxies_removed.is_empty()
            && self.proxies_modified.is_empty()
            && self.settings_changed.is_empty()
            && !self.listen_changed
    }

    pub fn requires_restart(&self) -> bool {
        self.listen_changed
    }
}
```

### Diff Function

```rust
pub fn diff_configs(old: &AppConfig, new: &AppConfig) -> ConfigDiff {
    let mut diff = ConfigDiff::default();

    // Compare proxy lists
    let old_ids: HashSet<_> = old.proxies.iter().map(|p| &p.id).collect();
    let new_ids: HashSet<_> = new.proxies.iter().map(|p| &p.id).collect();

    for id in new_ids.difference(&old_ids) {
        diff.proxies_added.push(id.to_string());
    }
    for id in old_ids.difference(&new_ids) {
        diff.proxies_removed.push(id.to_string());
    }

    // Compare settings
    if old.settings.health_check_interval_secs != new.settings.health_check_interval_secs {
        diff.settings_changed.push((
            "health_check_interval_secs".to_string(),
            old.settings.health_check_interval_secs.to_string(),
            new.settings.health_check_interval_secs.to_string(),
        ));
    }
    // ... more settings comparisons

    // Check listen address
    if old.listen != new.listen {
        diff.listen_changed = true;
    }

    diff
}
```

### Logging Integration

```rust
impl ConfigDiff {
    pub fn log(&self) {
        for id in &self.proxies_added {
            tracing::info!(proxy_id = %id, "Proxy added");
        }
        for id in &self.proxies_removed {
            tracing::info!(proxy_id = %id, "Proxy removed");
        }
        for (name, old, new) in &self.settings_changed {
            tracing::info!(setting = %name, old = %old, new = %new, "Setting changed");
        }
        if self.listen_changed {
            tracing::warn!("Listen address changed - restart required for this to take effect");
        }
    }
}
```

